      "side": 1,
      "message": "The spec here\nhttps://www.khronos.org/registry/egl/extensions/KHR/EGL_KHR_reusable_sync.txt\nfor eglClientWaitSyncKHR says that \nIf an error occurs then an error is generated and EGL_FALSE is returned.\nIsn\u0027t GL_WAIT_FAILED the way that the interface call indicates an error?  I would have thought that those would correspond.",
